documentType: FBI internal report or activity log
summary: This document appears to be an FBI internal log of significant activities, likely from the Violent Criminal Threat (VCT) Branch. It notes that an FBI Special Agent (SA) and an Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA) from the Southern District of New York (SDNY) will travel to West Palm Beach, Florida to interview a victim in support of an upcoming superseding indictment related to case 50D-NY-3027571.

keyFacts: The FBI's Violent Criminal Threat (VCT) Branch was involved in activities related to case 50D-NY-3027571.
An FBI Special Agent and an Assistant U.S. Attorney from SDNY planned to travel to West Palm Beach, Florida, from January 18 to January 21, 2021.
The purpose of the travel was to interview a victim in support of an upcoming superseding indictment.
The document is dated January 15, 2021, and appears to be an internal log of significant activities.
